            <div style="background: #e3f2fd; padding: 25px; border-radius: 8px; margin-bottom: 30px; border-left: 5px solid #2196f3;">
                <h3 style="color: #1976d2; margin-bottom: 15px;">ğŸ“Œ What is Izafe?</h3>
                <p style="line-height: 1.8; font-size: 1.05rem;">
                    The <strong>Izafe</strong> (also spelled Ezafe) is a <strong>linking particle</strong> used in Kurdish to connect:
                </p>
                <ul style="margin-left: 20px; margin-top: 10px; line-height: 1.8; font-size: 1.05rem;">
                    <li>A noun to another noun (possession, relationship)</li>
                    <li>A noun to an adjective (description)</li>
                    <li>A noun to a possessive pronoun</li>
                </ul>
                <p style="line-height: 1.8; font-size: 1.05rem; margin-top: 15px;">
                    It's similar to <strong>"of"</strong> in English or <strong>"de"</strong> in French, but it's a suffix attached to the first noun.
                </p>
            </div>

